===Etymology===
Named after the inventor, German chemist Richard Erlenmeyer, who created it in 1861.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[w:Richard August Carl Emil Erlenmeyer|Erlenmeyer]] [[flask]]}}

#{{context|chemistry}} A glass [[laboratory]] flask of a conical profile with a narrow tubular neck and a flat bottom, used to hold or mix or dissolve chemical compounds.
